00:38:57.270 --> 00:38:59.750
an interesting few months.

00:38:59.750 --> 00:39:03.630
This affects every relationship
because friends and family

00:39:03.630 --> 00:39:05.890
don't always agree.

00:39:05.890 --> 00:39:07.120
Excuse me.

00:39:07.120 --> 00:39:09.844
So insight.

00:39:09.844 --> 00:39:10.760
SHARON SALZBERG: Yeah.

00:39:10.760 --> 00:39:13.010
I wouldn't make assumptions
that everyone in this room

00:39:13.010 --> 00:39:16.370
agrees, you know,
or wherever you

00:39:16.370 --> 00:39:20.650
are, because that is also true.

00:39:20.650 --> 00:39:26.790
And I think there's another
way of understanding the term

00:39:26.790 --> 00:39:32.320
judgment, which is maybe not as
broad as our usual way, which

00:39:32.320 --> 00:39:34.510
is, I think, the way
you were using it.

00:39:34.510 --> 00:39:36.030
Because we have views.

00:39:36.030 --> 00:39:37.710
We have discernment.

00:39:37.710 --> 00:39:39.473
And there is such a
thing as ignorance.

00:39:43.650 --> 00:39:45.230
Any of us can have
some knowledge

00:39:45.230 --> 00:39:49.160
of how the universe works, and
hopefully growing knowledge

00:39:49.160 --> 00:39:52.000
of how the universe works.

00:39:52.000 --> 00:39:55.470
And if somebody is living
in defiance of that,

00:39:55.470 --> 00:39:59.687
then there's discordance
and there's suffering.

00:39:59.687 --> 00:40:00.520
It's just how it is.

00:40:00.520 --> 00:40:04.720
Like if you-- from the
meditative point of view,

00:40:04.720 --> 00:40:09.530
it would say if you completely
refute the idea of change,

00:40:09.530 --> 00:40:14.250
you refuse to admit that
we're all going to die,

00:40:14.250 --> 00:40:18.000
there's a society maxim
right there, right?

00:40:18.000 --> 00:40:20.470
Stay in control of
everything all the time.

00:40:20.470 --> 00:40:23.440
You can manage that.

00:40:23.440 --> 00:40:26.750
Don't admit any vulnerability,
because you should

00:40:26.750 --> 00:40:31.170
be ashamed of painful feeling.

00:40:31.170 --> 00:40:39.170
And/or you don't deserve to feel
good, to let in the pleasure,

00:40:39.170 --> 00:40:42.440
either because there's too
much suffering elsewhere,

00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:46.990
or you just don't deserve it.

00:40:46.990 --> 00:40:50.020
I mean, there's a million
things like that that

00:40:50.020 --> 00:40:51.870
are ignorant that we all have.

00:40:51.870 --> 00:40:58.650
And when they run our lives,
then we are suffering.

00:40:58.650 --> 00:41:04.670
That's why we suffer, is
because we're so out of sync.

00:41:04.670 --> 00:41:11.970
So there are some
almost scientific laws

00:41:11.970 --> 00:41:13.120
of the universe.

00:41:13.120 --> 00:41:15.916
Everything changes all the time.

00:41:15.916 --> 00:41:18.540
And we are all connected.

00:41:18.540 --> 00:41:20.700
We live in an
interconnected universe.

00:41:20.700 --> 00:41:24.890
So what happens to some
group of people over there,

00:41:24.890 --> 00:41:28.280
it never stays over there.

00:41:28.280 --> 00:41:29.579
It filters out over here.

00:41:29.579 --> 00:41:30.870
There is no over there anymore.

00:41:30.870 --> 00:41:33.480
And science shows us that.

00:41:33.480 --> 00:41:36.060
Environmental consciousness
shows us that.

00:41:36.060 --> 00:41:38.760
Even epidemiology shows that.

00:41:38.760 --> 00:41:40.960
Economics shows us that.

00:41:40.960 --> 00:41:42.950
We live in an
interconnected universe.

00:41:42.950 --> 00:41:48.830
So if you have a whole world
view that says that's not true,

00:41:48.830 --> 00:41:50.910
it's kind of scary.

00:41:50.910 --> 00:41:54.890
But that's different than
holding someone in contempt.

00:41:54.890 --> 00:41:56.390
So when we use
the word judgment,

00:41:56.390 --> 00:41:59.970
it's kind of specific.

00:41:59.970 --> 00:42:09.870
It's feeling contemptuous,
or it's feeling so superior

00:42:09.870 --> 00:42:13.460
that we can only
assume somebody is

00:42:13.460 --> 00:42:18.890
coming from a really
damaged place to have

00:42:18.890 --> 00:42:21.010
the view that they have.

00:42:21.010 --> 00:42:24.750
There are lots of ways in which
we separate very strongly.

00:42:24.750 --> 00:42:28.140
But that's one of the
fascinating things

00:42:28.140 --> 00:42:29.832
about compassion.

00:42:29.832 --> 00:42:32.040
There's like, how can you
have compassion for someone

00:42:32.040 --> 00:42:34.480
and really feel they're wrong?

00:42:34.480 --> 00:42:37.590
And do everything
you can to keep them

00:42:37.590 --> 00:42:45.040
from being able to
affectuate their,

00:42:45.040 --> 00:42:48.540
to your mind, wrong view.

00:42:48.540 --> 00:42:52.640
I don't know that I want
people who really completely

00:42:52.640 --> 00:42:57.620
disbelieve in interconnection
running climate

00:42:57.620 --> 00:43:02.180
policy, or anything, really.

00:43:05.620 --> 00:43:10.530
So I would work hard to try
to keep that from happening.

00:43:10.530 --> 00:43:13.510
And I don't think
that has to come

00:43:13.510 --> 00:43:18.980
from a place of real
hatred and alienation.

00:43:18.980 --> 00:43:23.830
It's always useful, I
think, to look at ourselves,

00:43:23.830 --> 00:43:30.390
and when we are the most
disconnected, what's

00:43:30.390 --> 00:43:33.300
cooking in there?

00:43:33.300 --> 00:43:41.930
And I hazard a guess that
we would find layers of fear

00:43:41.930 --> 00:43:43.300
in ourselves.

00:43:43.300 --> 00:43:46.950
And I would probably make
that assumption about others.

00:43:46.950 --> 00:43:49.076
And I personally have not
been watching anything,

00:43:49.076 --> 00:43:52.230
but I have a book deadline.

00:43:52.230 --> 00:43:53.730
PHOENIX SOLEIL: Can
I say something?

00:43:53.730 --> 00:43:55.755
SHARON SALZBERG: Please.

00:43:55.755 --> 00:43:57.130
PHOENIX SOLEIL:
I think this goes

00:43:57.130 --> 00:44:03.940
at the heart of one of
the gifts of meditation,

00:44:03.940 --> 00:44:07.170
is being able to
hold the paradox.

00:44:07.170 --> 00:44:09.780
I think what scares
people sometimes

00:44:09.780 --> 00:44:14.220
about doing healing work is,
well, I'm going to be removed.

00:44:14.220 --> 00:44:18.350
And is it OK that I
can have my safe life

00:44:18.350 --> 00:44:25.080
and care for my loved ones when
so many horrible situations

00:44:25.080 --> 00:44:26.740
in the world and
the environment.

00:44:26.740 --> 00:44:29.660
And it's about,
can you hold both?

00:44:29.660 --> 00:44:33.620
Because actually, the
thing is that the stronger

00:44:33.620 --> 00:44:38.730
you are and the
more able you are,

00:44:38.730 --> 00:44:43.280
the more you can bring to the
difficult things in the world.

00:44:43.280 --> 00:44:46.830
But what some people can do
is try to isolate themselves.

00:44:46.830 --> 00:44:51.150
And so it requires that strength
of being able to see both.

00:44:51.150 --> 00:44:56.240
When you saw the judgment,
being able to also see the fear,

00:44:56.240 --> 00:45:00.320
and to be able to see, oh yeah,
I could focus on this thought.

00:45:00.320 --> 00:45:02.780
And that's what a lot of
us would do, is focus on,

00:45:02.780 --> 00:45:05.190
this is all the ways
that they're wrong.

00:45:05.190 --> 00:45:08.040
And you take a
breath, and then you

00:45:08.040 --> 00:45:09.880
notice, well, there's
a sensation of pain.

00:45:09.880 --> 00:45:14.980
There's also this feeling
of my feet on the ground.

00:45:14.980 --> 00:45:16.560
There's the fact
that I'm breathing.

00:45:16.560 --> 00:45:19.650
There's all of these things
happening at the same time.

00:45:19.650 --> 00:45:22.820
And that is actual
health, is being

00:45:22.820 --> 00:45:27.310
able to see and hold all of that
complexity, because when you

00:45:27.310 --> 00:45:30.850
hold all that complexity,
instead of being overwhelmed

00:45:30.850 --> 00:45:35.520
by, wow, this person is so
judgmental, you can hold,

00:45:35.520 --> 00:45:38.280
yes, and we're all human
and we all have this.

00:45:38.280 --> 00:45:40.700
And we also have
this vulnerability.

00:45:40.700 --> 00:45:45.010
And we also have this incredible
urge to help each other.

00:45:45.010 --> 00:45:47.380
Being able to hold that
thought at the same time

00:45:47.380 --> 00:45:50.580
that you're holding the thought
of this particular human

00:45:50.580 --> 00:45:55.030
being being so
difficult to be with,

00:45:55.030 --> 00:45:57.650
that's being able
to hold a paradox.

00:45:57.650 --> 00:46:01.200
And the other tool
I would bring is

00:46:01.200 --> 00:46:06.280
that with nonviolent
communication, a lot of times

00:46:06.280 --> 00:46:09.370
we have this thing called
translating the judgment.

00:46:09.370 --> 00:46:12.060
A lot of times when
there's a strong judgment,

00:46:12.060 --> 00:46:14.900
there's this need, this
beautiful human need

00:46:14.900 --> 00:46:17.450
that's not being met.

00:46:17.450 --> 00:46:20.410
And when you get to
that need, then it

00:46:20.410 --> 00:46:24.150
changes your perspective,
because then instead

00:46:24.150 --> 00:46:26.190
of focusing on
what's not working,

00:46:26.190 --> 00:46:28.600
you're focusing
on what you want.

00:46:28.600 --> 00:46:31.230
And that can be liberating.

00:46:31.230 --> 00:46:34.430
AUDIENCE: One of the things
